HEADWORD: Buccinator
<hw>Buc`ci*na"tor</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a
trumpeter, fr. <ets>bucinare</ets> to sound the trumpet.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A muscle of the cheek; -- so called from its use
in blowing wind instruments.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buccinoid</ent>⟦br⟧
